title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: The current implementation of the getcolumnlabel method in the meta data object does not return user recognizable strings.
EB: The getcolumnlabel method in the meta data object should return user recognizable strings. This is important because the labels need to be displayed to the end user before doing the extraction. The getcolumnlabel method should return the same labels as after extraction.
SR:
1. Create a meta data object.
2. Call the getcolumnlabel method on the meta data object.
3. Verify that the returned value is a user recognizable string.
